00:00:19.670 --> 00:00:22.400 align:middle line:10%
>> Today on "Cosmic Disclosure,"
we are talking about weapons

00:00:22.400 --> 00:00:24.950 align:middle line:10%
of the SSP with Randy Cramer.

00:00:24.950 --> 00:00:26.270 align:middle line:90%
Randy, welcome.

00:00:26.270 --> 00:00:27.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, thank you.

00:00:27.380 --> 00:00:29.630 align:middle line:84%
>> From what you have seen
from other plants and ET

00:00:29.630 --> 00:00:33.920 align:middle line:84%
civilizations, are they more or
less peaceful than what we know

00:00:33.920 --> 00:00:35.053 align:middle line:90%
here on Earth?

00:00:35.053 --> 00:00:36.470 align:middle line:10%
>> There's just a
variation there.

00:00:36.470 --> 00:00:42.620 align:middle line:10%
So you have species who are
better at aggression, better

00:00:42.620 --> 00:00:44.660 align:middle line:10%
at war than others.

00:00:44.660 --> 00:00:48.000 align:middle line:84%
I mean, aggression
is a genetic trait,

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.000 align:middle line:84%
and there are species who
have higher aggression

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:53.120 align:middle line:84%
levels, species who have lower
aggression levels, species

00:00:53.120 --> 00:00:57.290 align:middle line:84%
who've evolved out
their aggression levels.

00:00:57.290 --> 00:00:59.900 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's as
many possibilities

00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:00.740 align:middle line:90%
as you can think of.

00:01:00.740 --> 00:01:05.420 align:middle line:84%
So what we find out there is
there are many species who

00:01:05.420 --> 00:01:07.890 align:middle line:84%
are happy to pick up
a weapon and fight,

00:01:07.890 --> 00:01:09.713 align:middle line:84%
and there are a lot
of species too that

00:01:09.713 --> 00:01:10.880 align:middle line:90%
just aren't that good at it.

00:01:10.880 --> 00:01:14.840 align:middle line:84%
So they either would rather
have someone else do it for them

00:01:14.840 --> 00:01:18.170 align:middle line:84%
or get their butt kicked because
they're just not good at it.

00:01:18.170 --> 00:01:20.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, even if they are
peaceful civilizations,

00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:23.910 align:middle line:84%
how important is it for them and
their society to actually have

00:01:23.910 --> 00:01:24.710 align:middle line:90%
weapons?

00:01:24.710 --> 00:01:25.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly.

00:01:25.310 --> 00:01:27.170 align:middle line:84%
For some of them, it's
just not that important

00:01:27.170 --> 00:01:29.120 align:middle line:84%
until something happens,
and then all of a sudden,

00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:29.450 align:middle line:90%
they need it.

00:01:29.450 --> 00:01:30.950 align:middle line:90%
They're not expansionist.

00:01:30.950 --> 00:01:34.580 align:middle line:84%
They're not trying to
colonize far and wide

00:01:34.580 --> 00:01:36.218 align:middle line:90%
into hostile territory.

00:01:36.218 --> 00:01:38.510 align:middle line:84%
They're really just concerned
about planetary security.

00:01:38.510 --> 00:01:42.603 align:middle line:84%
So mostly, their security
forces keep the peace

00:01:42.603 --> 00:01:44.270 align:middle line:84%
but aren't going to
be able to withstand

00:01:44.270 --> 00:01:47.390 align:middle line:84%
an invasion or any kind of
hostile military action.

00:01:47.390 --> 00:01:49.340 align:middle line:84%
They're just not trained
for it or equipped.

00:01:49.340 --> 00:01:52.940 align:middle line:84%
>> As a soldier, tell us some of
the weapons that you employed.

00:01:52.940 --> 00:01:56.420 align:middle line:84%
>> My favorite is the railgun,
because it's the most accurate

00:01:56.420 --> 00:01:59.630 align:middle line:90%
over the longest distance.

00:01:59.630 --> 00:02:02.390 align:middle line:84%
For anyone who's fired
a normal firearm,

00:02:02.390 --> 00:02:08.360 align:middle line:84%
imagine a rifle that doesn't
kick and stays straight

00:02:08.360 --> 00:02:13.280 align:middle line:90%
and shoots motionless variants--

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:15.860 align:middle line:84%
no kick, no shake,
right out the barrel--

00:02:15.860 --> 00:02:17.450 align:middle line:84%
one, two, three,
right after another.

00:02:17.450 --> 00:02:19.250 align:middle line:90%
So they're incredibly accurate.

00:02:19.250 --> 00:02:22.400 align:middle line:84%
They don't heat up like
a chemically propelled

00:02:22.400 --> 00:02:23.775 align:middle line:90%
projectile does.

00:02:23.775 --> 00:02:24.900 align:middle line:90%
They're really my favorite.

00:02:24.900 --> 00:02:28.720 align:middle line:84%
You've got the greatest, longest
straight shot over a distance.

00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:31.130 align:middle line:84%
>> I do have a little bit
of experience with these,

00:02:31.130 --> 00:02:33.350 align:middle line:90%
and they are electromagnetic.

00:02:33.350 --> 00:02:34.192 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:02:34.192 --> 00:02:36.650 align:middle line:84%
>> Maybe you can explain to us
how does that work with that

00:02:36.650 --> 00:02:39.330 align:middle line:84%
projectile and how
the charge works.

00:02:39.330 --> 00:02:40.130 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:02:40.130 --> 00:02:42.890 align:middle line:84%
So if the barrel
is about this long,

00:02:42.890 --> 00:02:45.020 align:middle line:84%
you have a series
of electromagnets

00:02:45.020 --> 00:02:46.880 align:middle line:90%
that go along the barrel.

00:02:46.880 --> 00:02:50.090 align:middle line:84%
So they're all in the off
position, and the projectile,

00:02:50.090 --> 00:02:54.330 align:middle line:84%
which again is a metal magnetic
projectile that goes here--

00:02:54.330 --> 00:02:57.500 align:middle line:84%
so the first
electromagnetic is turned on

00:02:57.500 --> 00:03:00.710 align:middle line:84%
to create a magnetic field that
holds on to the projectile.

00:03:00.710 --> 00:03:03.230 align:middle line:84%
And then the next
magnet in front of it

00:03:03.230 --> 00:03:06.890 align:middle line:84%
is turned on at the same time
that the magnet behind it

00:03:06.890 --> 00:03:07.880 align:middle line:90%
is turned off.

00:03:07.880 --> 00:03:11.000 align:middle line:84%
And that all happens in about
a nanosecond from here to here.

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:14.757 align:middle line:84%
So very, very quickly, as each
subsequent magnet turns on

00:03:14.757 --> 00:03:17.090 align:middle line:84%
and the one behind it turns
off, it grabs the projectile

00:03:17.090 --> 00:03:20.190 align:middle line:84%
and pulls it down the rail
and then fires it out the end.

00:03:20.190 --> 00:03:22.350 align:middle line:84%
But again, it happens
in a nanosecond.

00:03:22.350 --> 00:03:26.090 align:middle line:84%
So it just pulls it super
fast straight down the barrel

00:03:26.090 --> 00:03:28.290 align:middle line:90%
without an explosion.

00:03:28.290 --> 00:03:30.270 align:middle line:84%
And again, so there's
less heat, no kick.

00:03:30.270 --> 00:03:31.070 align:middle line:90%
They're fragments.

00:03:31.070 --> 00:03:32.340 align:middle line:90%
>> What do they look like?

00:03:32.340 --> 00:03:34.492 align:middle line:90%
Do they have rifles and pistols?

00:03:34.492 --> 00:03:35.450 align:middle line:90%
What do they look like?

00:03:35.450 --> 00:03:41.750 align:middle line:84%
>> To be honest, they look
like a fairly normal rifle--

00:03:41.750 --> 00:03:47.660 align:middle line:84%
I mean, a little fancier,
but a main housing,

00:03:47.660 --> 00:03:50.330 align:middle line:84%
a stock with a
pistol grip if it's

00:03:50.330 --> 00:03:53.180 align:middle line:84%
something you're holding
in your hand with a stock

00:03:53.180 --> 00:03:54.440 align:middle line:90%
and a barrel on it.

00:03:54.440 --> 00:03:57.500 align:middle line:84%
Some of them have a
pistol grip down here.

00:03:57.500 --> 00:04:01.640 align:middle line:84%
That's if the rifle is
not attached to your suit.

00:04:01.640 --> 00:04:03.200 align:middle line:84%
One of the more
advanced exosuits

00:04:03.200 --> 00:04:07.790 align:middle line:84%
has it mounted on the right arm,
so all you have to do is point.

00:04:07.790 --> 00:04:09.200 align:middle line:90%
>> How do you aim with it, then?

00:04:09.200 --> 00:04:11.690 align:middle line:84%
Is it just like we
utilize our rifles today?

00:04:11.690 --> 00:04:15.500 align:middle line:84%
So it actually has a
laser-guided system

00:04:15.500 --> 00:04:17.720 align:middle line:90%
that shows up in your HUD.

00:04:17.720 --> 00:04:20.839 align:middle line:84%
So you can hip shoot
very accurately,

00:04:20.839 --> 00:04:23.180 align:middle line:84%
because your HUD is
telling you exactly

00:04:23.180 --> 00:04:27.810 align:middle line:84%
where your reticle from the
laser pointer on the weapon

00:04:27.810 --> 00:04:28.610 align:middle line:90%
are pointing at.

00:04:28.610 --> 00:04:33.140 align:middle line:84%
So in some cases,
with the one that

00:04:33.140 --> 00:04:35.120 align:middle line:84%
has a full stock
body on it, there's

00:04:35.120 --> 00:04:40.650 align:middle line:84%
a scope that you can use,
but it's not required.

00:04:40.650 --> 00:04:42.650 align:middle line:84%
If you want to see something
for a long distance

00:04:42.650 --> 00:04:44.420 align:middle line:84%
and get a close up
shot, use the scope.

00:04:44.420 --> 00:04:47.420 align:middle line:84%
But anything within 100 yards
or so, you can just pull up

00:04:47.420 --> 00:04:50.222 align:middle line:84%
your hip shoot, and your
reticle on your heads up display

00:04:50.222 --> 00:04:52.430 align:middle line:84%
will show you exactly where
you're going to hit and--

00:04:52.430 --> 00:04:53.720 align:middle line:90%
[SHOOTING NOISES] yeah.

00:04:53.720 --> 00:04:57.250 align:middle line:84%
>> How many rounds
do these railguns--

00:04:57.250 --> 00:04:59.290 align:middle line:84%
the handheld railguns,
I should say, too.

00:04:59.290 --> 00:05:00.090 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:00.090 --> 00:05:04.490 align:middle line:90%
Usually, there's an ammo box--

00:05:04.490 --> 00:05:07.100 align:middle line:84%
we refer to as a clip even
though it's not a clip--

00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:09.842 align:middle line:84%
which usually holds
about 100 rounds.

00:05:09.842 --> 00:05:11.300 align:middle line:84%
>> What are the
rounds made out of?

00:05:11.300 --> 00:05:15.120 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a metal alloy
that's harder than uranium.

00:05:15.120 --> 00:05:18.080 align:middle line:84%
So instead of using a
Sabot round to puncture--

00:05:18.080 --> 00:05:21.160 align:middle line:84%
whatever this is made out of,
some really, really tough alloy

00:05:21.160 --> 00:05:23.190 align:middle line:84%
that punctures
through most armor.

00:05:23.190 --> 00:05:25.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, our current military
actually has cannons like this,

00:05:25.910 --> 00:05:26.710 align:middle line:90%
correct?

00:05:26.710 --> 00:05:27.510 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah.

00:05:27.510 --> 00:05:29.230 align:middle line:84%
The Navy has been
putting railguns

00:05:29.230 --> 00:05:31.510 align:middle line:90%
on ships for a few years now.

00:05:31.510 --> 00:05:34.990 align:middle line:84%
They had their first destroyer
roll out a few years ago

00:05:34.990 --> 00:05:36.342 align:middle line:90%
with railguns on them.

00:05:36.342 --> 00:05:38.050 align:middle line:84%
And then I think I
just read that they're

00:05:38.050 --> 00:05:41.980 align:middle line:84%
starting to put energy
projected weapons that

00:05:41.980 --> 00:05:44.140 align:middle line:84%
can shoot planes and
missiles out of the sky too.

00:05:44.140 --> 00:05:47.260 align:middle line:10%
So the Navy ships right now are
being equipped with railguns

00:05:47.260 --> 00:05:50.170 align:middle line:10%
and directed energy weapons.

00:05:50.170 --> 00:05:52.750 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, tell us more
about these plasma rifles

00:05:52.750 --> 00:05:54.190 align:middle line:90%
you've mentioned in the past.

00:05:54.190 --> 00:05:59.110 align:middle line:84%
>> So the plasma rifle
takes a super, super hot,

00:05:59.110 --> 00:06:02.830 align:middle line:84%
heated ball of plasma, puts it
in a contained electromagnetic

00:06:02.830 --> 00:06:08.650 align:middle line:84%
field, and then again, launches
it down a rail that guides it

00:06:08.650 --> 00:06:10.660 align:middle line:84%
and sends it out
the end of the gun,

00:06:10.660 --> 00:06:14.830 align:middle line:84%
which I'm told that it's several
thousand feet per second.

00:06:14.830 --> 00:06:18.250 align:middle line:84%
The range is dependent
on the sustainability

00:06:18.250 --> 00:06:19.760 align:middle line:90%
of the electromagnetic field.

00:06:19.760 --> 00:06:23.980 align:middle line:84%
So few hundred yards out,
the electromagnetic field

00:06:23.980 --> 00:06:27.460 align:middle line:84%
dissipates, and that causes
the plasma ball to dissipate.

00:06:27.460 --> 00:06:30.400 align:middle line:84%
But anything within that first
couple yards is going to get

00:06:30.400 --> 00:06:36.790 align:middle line:84%
hit with a 5,000-degree hot
ball of plasma that will burn

00:06:36.790 --> 00:06:38.450 align:middle line:84%
and melt through
just about anything.

00:06:38.450 --> 00:06:40.930 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, on the missions that
you've been on, when would you

00:06:40.930 --> 00:06:43.520 align:middle line:84%
choose a plasma
rifle over a railgun?

00:06:43.520 --> 00:06:45.310 align:middle line:84%
>> It usually
wouldn't be my choice.

00:06:45.310 --> 00:06:50.260 align:middle line:84%
It would be a matter of whether
they felt like the railgun was

00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:52.750 align:middle line:84%
going to be the most effective
close-up weapon if we were

00:06:52.750 --> 00:06:54.760 align:middle line:84%
going to be in close
quarters combat,

00:06:54.760 --> 00:06:57.850 align:middle line:84%
or if we were going to need the
extended range of the railgun,

00:06:57.850 --> 00:06:59.890 align:middle line:84%
or if it was going to be
something that was just

00:06:59.890 --> 00:07:03.310 align:middle line:84%
going to likely be nothing more
than a couple hundred yards.

00:07:03.310 --> 00:07:05.878 align:middle line:84%
It's decided based
on other criteria

00:07:05.878 --> 00:07:07.420 align:middle line:84%
that we're not
deciding in the field.

00:07:07.420 --> 00:07:12.040 align:middle line:84%
So it's decided by intelligence
personnel and command officers

00:07:12.040 --> 00:07:14.300 align:middle line:84%
way before we're ever
put in the field,

00:07:14.300 --> 00:07:16.420 align:middle line:84%
and they tell us which
one we're going to carry.

00:07:16.420 --> 00:07:18.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, what defensive systems
would you have against these

00:07:18.880 --> 00:07:21.520 align:middle line:90%
if your opponent had them?

00:07:21.520 --> 00:07:24.160 align:middle line:84%
>> There is a personal
shielding that can deflect them.

00:07:24.160 --> 00:07:26.500 align:middle line:84%
It's essentially an
electromagnetic shield

00:07:26.500 --> 00:07:29.380 align:middle line:90%
that will basically--

00:07:29.380 --> 00:07:31.750 align:middle line:84%
like north pole north
pole on a magnet

00:07:31.750 --> 00:07:36.190 align:middle line:84%
will cause to deflect a
magnetically contained

00:07:36.190 --> 00:07:38.845 align:middle line:84%
ball of hot plasma, as it hits
the shield, will bounce off.

00:07:38.845 --> 00:07:40.720 align:middle line:84%
It does the same thing
to a metal projectile,

00:07:40.720 --> 00:07:41.520 align:middle line:90%
actually, too.

00:07:41.520 --> 00:07:45.730 align:middle line:84%
>> And what device is that
that's on you that allows that

00:07:45.730 --> 00:07:46.690 align:middle line:90%
to be eminating?

00:07:46.690 --> 00:07:49.000 align:middle line:84%
I'm assuming it's an
electromagnetic toroidal field

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:50.950 align:middle line:84%
around you that
blocks everything.

00:07:50.950 --> 00:07:54.550 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, it's a shield generator
that's usually in the pack.

00:07:54.550 --> 00:07:58.330 align:middle line:84%
The pack is the back
portion of the suit, which

00:07:58.330 --> 00:08:00.130 align:middle line:84%
is where the power
system is contained,

00:08:00.130 --> 00:08:01.750 align:middle line:84%
the circulation
system is contained,

00:08:01.750 --> 00:08:04.840 align:middle line:84%
and any other
systems that aren't

00:08:04.840 --> 00:08:07.240 align:middle line:84%
local somewhere in the
suit are all in the pack.

00:08:07.240 --> 00:08:10.000 align:middle line:84%
>> You seem to have a lot of
electronics on these suits that

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:11.850 align:middle line:90%
you're talking about.

00:08:11.850 --> 00:08:15.130 align:middle line:84%
Is there any risk for
radiation or electromagnetic

00:08:15.130 --> 00:08:17.620 align:middle line:84%
pulse from these suits
that could cause your cells

00:08:17.620 --> 00:08:21.310 align:middle line:90%
and your DNA to be damaged?

00:08:21.310 --> 00:08:23.800 align:middle line:84%
>> They have a really good
radiation shielding on them,

00:08:23.800 --> 00:08:28.820 align:middle line:84%
so the radiation would have
to be really, really high.

00:08:28.820 --> 00:08:33.950 align:middle line:84%
But yeah, I mean,
electromagnetic pulse

00:08:33.950 --> 00:08:36.090 align:middle line:90%
is a risk at that point.

00:08:36.090 --> 00:08:40.850 align:middle line:84%
And so it wouldn't be the
first time or the last time

00:08:40.850 --> 00:08:42.770 align:middle line:84%
that someone was
wearing an exosuit that

00:08:42.770 --> 00:08:46.740 align:middle line:84%
had to jump out of it because
it was no longer operational.

00:08:46.740 --> 00:08:51.380 align:middle line:84%
So in the larger suits, we
call the papa bear suit,

00:08:51.380 --> 00:08:53.245 align:middle line:84%
flip of a button, and
the thing pops open,

00:08:53.245 --> 00:08:54.620 align:middle line:84%
and you can jump
right out of it.

00:08:54.620 --> 00:08:55.610 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:08:55.610 --> 00:08:58.850 align:middle line:84%
>> During the break, we
got into the exosuits,

00:08:58.850 --> 00:09:01.200 align:middle line:84%
and I'd like to talk about
those a little bit more.

00:09:01.200 --> 00:09:05.130 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to talk about, number
one, what do they look like?

00:09:05.130 --> 00:09:06.860 align:middle line:90%
How do you enter them?

00:09:06.860 --> 00:09:08.930 align:middle line:84%
And what's the power
supply for them?

00:09:08.930 --> 00:09:11.030 align:middle line:90%
Is that also with the pack?

00:09:11.030 --> 00:09:13.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, yeah, definitely.

00:09:13.460 --> 00:09:16.430 align:middle line:84%
I'm not 100% sure what
the power system is other

00:09:16.430 --> 00:09:20.180 align:middle line:84%
than over time, I've seen them
change as far as the size.

00:09:20.180 --> 00:09:24.350 align:middle line:84%
So a couple decades
early in my career,

00:09:24.350 --> 00:09:29.150 align:middle line:84%
the power supply was about
the size of a shoe box.

00:09:29.150 --> 00:09:32.240 align:middle line:84%
Towards the end of my
career, the power supplies

00:09:32.240 --> 00:09:34.820 align:middle line:84%
were closer to the size
of a pack of cigarettes.

00:09:34.820 --> 00:09:37.990 align:middle line:84%
>> And what kind of
power supply is that?

00:09:37.990 --> 00:09:39.560 align:middle line:84%
Where's it getting
that energy from?

00:09:39.560 --> 00:09:43.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Usually a zero point or an
electron pump of some kind.

00:09:43.200 --> 00:09:46.760 align:middle line:84%
So there's something that can
continually pull out joules

00:09:46.760 --> 00:09:50.130 align:middle line:84%
pretty much forever until
the system itself is damaged.

00:09:50.130 --> 00:09:53.230 align:middle line:84%
But they're small, so you
can't build a bomb out

00:09:53.230 --> 00:09:54.040 align:middle line:90%
of them, really.

00:09:54.040 --> 00:09:55.873 align:middle line:84%
>> Through your experience
on your missions,

00:09:55.873 --> 00:09:59.380 align:middle line:84%
has there ever been a time that
your weapons failed against

00:09:59.380 --> 00:10:00.370 align:middle line:90%
an opponent?

00:10:00.370 --> 00:10:02.590 align:middle line:84%
>> It's incredibly
rare, incredibly rare.

00:10:02.590 --> 00:10:06.830 align:middle line:84%
The failure rate of the
equipment is less than 1%,

00:10:06.830 --> 00:10:08.440 align:middle line:84%
and there are very
few situations

00:10:08.440 --> 00:10:11.950 align:middle line:84%
that we would encounter--
again, because of our good intel

00:10:11.950 --> 00:10:13.510 align:middle line:84%
on what we're going
into, we don't

00:10:13.510 --> 00:10:15.370 align:middle line:84%
go into a situation
with equipment

00:10:15.370 --> 00:10:17.620 align:middle line:84%
that we have a sense is
not going to work well.

00:10:17.620 --> 00:10:20.860 align:middle line:84%
So we have a few variations
in the type of equipment

00:10:20.860 --> 00:10:25.330 align:middle line:84%
that we can use to be mission
ready for different defensive

00:10:25.330 --> 00:10:26.170 align:middle line:90%
circumstances.

00:10:26.170 --> 00:10:28.450 align:middle line:84%
So if we think that
electromagnetic pulse is

00:10:28.450 --> 00:10:29.470 align:middle line:90%
an option--

00:10:29.470 --> 00:10:31.300 align:middle line:84%
our likely defensive
option, we're not

00:10:31.300 --> 00:10:32.860 align:middle line:90%
going to use certain exosuits.

00:10:32.860 --> 00:10:34.900 align:middle line:84%
We might use
something different.

00:10:34.900 --> 00:10:41.020 align:middle line:84%
>> Were any of those weapons
ineffective during a combat

00:10:41.020 --> 00:10:45.053 align:middle line:84%
moment where, oh,
it's not firing?

00:10:45.053 --> 00:10:47.470 align:middle line:84%
>> There were a couple of times
when we were engaging with

00:10:47.470 --> 00:10:50.575 align:middle line:90%
the indigenous reptoids on Mars.

00:10:50.575 --> 00:10:53.230 align:middle line:84%
And we know after
the fact that they

00:10:53.230 --> 00:10:56.980 align:middle line:84%
were using psionic
abilities, so it would often

00:10:56.980 --> 00:10:59.890 align:middle line:84%
be that we could not
hit them from a distance

00:10:59.890 --> 00:11:01.780 align:middle line:84%
or the weapons wouldn't
work at a distance.

00:11:01.780 --> 00:11:03.550 align:middle line:84%
And we would have to get
closer and closer and closer,

00:11:03.550 --> 00:11:05.300 align:middle line:84%
because they wanted
close-quarters combat.

00:11:05.300 --> 00:11:09.840 align:middle line:84%
So we would find the
inconsistent operational rates

00:11:09.840 --> 00:11:11.842 align:middle line:90%
at a distance were up and down.

00:11:11.842 --> 00:11:13.300 align:middle line:84%
And because they
were inconsistent,

00:11:13.300 --> 00:11:19.330 align:middle line:84%
we didn't think it was
mechanical failure or that 1%

00:11:19.330 --> 00:11:21.235 align:middle line:90%
of manufacturing defects.

00:11:21.235 --> 00:11:22.610 align:middle line:84%
We figured it was
something else.

00:11:22.610 --> 00:11:24.340 align:middle line:84%
But it took some time
before we learned

00:11:24.340 --> 00:11:26.230 align:middle line:90%
that it was psionic abilities.

00:11:26.230 --> 00:11:29.440 align:middle line:84%
>> Once, you have mentioned
to me about the scorpions,

00:11:29.440 --> 00:11:30.640 align:middle line:90%
these giant creatures.

00:11:30.640 --> 00:11:32.800 align:middle line:84%
What were you using
against them as far

00:11:32.800 --> 00:11:34.960 align:middle line:90%
as weapons and protection?

00:11:34.960 --> 00:11:37.870 align:middle line:10%
>> Railgun, body armor,
personal shield--

00:11:37.870 --> 00:11:39.900 align:middle line:10%
that was about it.

00:11:39.900 --> 00:11:41.690 align:middle line:84%
So again, it was
fairly effective,

00:11:41.690 --> 00:11:43.440 align:middle line:84%
we were just overwhelmed
by their numbers.

00:11:43.440 --> 00:11:45.480 align:middle line:84%
If there were less
of them, I think

00:11:45.480 --> 00:11:47.520 align:middle line:84%
we could have handled
them, but when

00:11:47.520 --> 00:11:50.460 align:middle line:84%
you're outnumbered 20 to 1,
it starts to get difficult.

00:11:50.460 --> 00:11:54.480 align:middle line:84%
>> And these railguns
have an automatic setting?

00:11:54.480 --> 00:11:57.030 align:middle line:84%
What kind of settings do
the guns have on them?

00:11:57.030 --> 00:11:58.680 align:middle line:90%
>> The weapon itself--

00:11:58.680 --> 00:12:02.250 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the single shot,
triburst, full-auto--

00:12:02.250 --> 00:12:05.820 align:middle line:90%
I mean, there's that option.

00:12:05.820 --> 00:12:10.890 align:middle line:84%
There is also a difference
in the projectile.

00:12:10.890 --> 00:12:15.720 align:middle line:84%
So we had air burst ammo,
which is essentially

00:12:15.720 --> 00:12:18.270 align:middle line:84%
a projectile that's made up of
many, many little parts that

00:12:18.270 --> 00:12:21.760 align:middle line:84%
are held together by this
electromagnetic field,

00:12:21.760 --> 00:12:24.600 align:middle line:84%
so then when it flies out of
the barrel, it breaks apart,

00:12:24.600 --> 00:12:28.110 align:middle line:84%
and you get a lot of little
projectiles flying out the end.

00:12:28.110 --> 00:12:28.910 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:12:28.910 --> 00:12:30.330 align:middle line:90%
>> Kind of like a cluster bomb.

00:12:30.330 --> 00:12:32.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, basically like a
little cluster bomb on the end

00:12:32.880 --> 00:12:33.690 align:middle line:90%
of a bullet.

00:12:33.690 --> 00:12:37.140 align:middle line:84%
So it's way more
powerful than a shotgun.

00:12:37.140 --> 00:12:41.730 align:middle line:84%
An air burst that breaks apart
three feet in front of someone

00:12:41.730 --> 00:12:44.810 align:middle line:84%
will completely tear
their upper body apart.

00:12:44.810 --> 00:12:47.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Like on the planes and the
helicopters where they have

00:12:47.840 --> 00:12:50.460 align:middle line:84%
the chaff that shoots
out and discombobulates,

00:12:50.460 --> 00:12:53.370 align:middle line:84%
is there weapons and is
there ammo that you can put

00:12:53.370 --> 00:12:55.420 align:middle line:84%
in your weapons
to discombobulate

00:12:55.420 --> 00:12:57.900 align:middle line:84%
extraterrestrials' sonic
abilities that would distort

00:12:57.900 --> 00:12:58.290 align:middle line:90%
them?

00:12:58.290 --> 00:12:59.310 align:middle line:90%
>> We did not have any.

00:12:59.310 --> 00:13:03.120 align:middle line:84%
We did not have specific weapons
that were for that purpose.

00:13:03.120 --> 00:13:07.880 align:middle line:84%
There were drones and
frequency emitters

00:13:07.880 --> 00:13:10.250 align:middle line:84%
that the intel teams
would sometimes use,

00:13:10.250 --> 00:13:13.500 align:middle line:84%
but that's not something
I'm too familiar with.

00:13:13.500 --> 00:13:19.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Were the extraterrestrial
weapons ever just far exceeded

00:13:19.250 --> 00:13:21.680 align:middle line:84%
the technology we
had of those weapons?

00:13:21.680 --> 00:13:25.430 align:middle line:84%
>> There was this one time when
there was a species that was

00:13:25.430 --> 00:13:27.140 align:middle line:90%
using a weapon that--

00:13:27.140 --> 00:13:30.520 align:middle line:90%


00:13:30.520 --> 00:13:32.370 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how
else to explain it--

00:13:32.370 --> 00:13:34.860 align:middle line:84%
if I was to point the
weapon at you and fire it,

00:13:34.860 --> 00:13:38.190 align:middle line:84%
it would take all of
the water in your body

00:13:38.190 --> 00:13:40.480 align:middle line:90%
and move it to another time.

00:13:40.480 --> 00:13:44.310 align:middle line:84%
So it's a temporal weapon
that takes your water out

00:13:44.310 --> 00:13:46.600 align:middle line:84%
of your body and moves it
to another part in time.

00:13:46.600 --> 00:13:49.080 align:middle line:84%
So all you're left with
is the dry molecules,

00:13:49.080 --> 00:13:53.150 align:middle line:84%
so you're instantly
dehydrated and turned to dust.

00:13:53.150 --> 00:13:55.380 align:middle line:84%
>> You're instantly just
a couple grams of powder.

00:13:55.380 --> 00:13:56.822 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:13:56.822 --> 00:13:58.030 align:middle line:90%
Poof.

00:13:58.030 --> 00:13:58.830 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:13:58.830 --> 00:13:59.660 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:13:59.660 --> 00:14:01.887 align:middle line:84%
So that's an
interdimensional weapon, huh?

00:14:01.887 --> 00:14:02.970 align:middle line:90%
>> It's a temporal weapon.

00:14:02.970 --> 00:14:04.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Temporal weapon.

00:14:04.080 --> 00:14:04.900 align:middle line:90%
What's that mean?

00:14:04.900 --> 00:14:07.200 align:middle line:84%
>> That means it's using
temporal mechanics--

00:14:07.200 --> 00:14:09.130 align:middle line:90%
the mechanics of time--

00:14:09.130 --> 00:14:09.930 align:middle line:90%
to operate.

00:14:09.930 --> 00:14:15.000 align:middle line:84%
Like I said, it's basically time
traveling the water molecules

00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:17.070 align:middle line:90%
in your body to somewhere else.

00:14:17.070 --> 00:14:21.080 align:middle line:84%
Which to me, I always think
about the other effect of it.

00:14:21.080 --> 00:14:24.120 align:middle line:84%
So somewhere, someone
is standing there,

00:14:24.120 --> 00:14:26.940 align:middle line:84%
and all of a sudden there's
your water somewhere,

00:14:26.940 --> 00:14:28.490 align:middle line:84%
and then it just
falls to the ground.

00:14:28.490 --> 00:14:29.490 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, what was that?

00:14:29.490 --> 00:14:31.050 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:14:31.050 --> 00:14:34.140 align:middle line:84%
So somewhere, your water ends
up where your body is not,

00:14:34.140 --> 00:14:37.110 align:middle line:84%
and your body turns to
dust, and your water

00:14:37.110 --> 00:14:39.120 align:middle line:90%
is then without a body.

00:14:39.120 --> 00:14:42.870 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, I was working on some
projects in New York where they

00:14:42.870 --> 00:14:47.310 align:middle line:84%
were utilizing technology just
to remove toxins in the body

00:14:47.310 --> 00:14:48.910 align:middle line:90%
and cancers.

00:14:48.910 --> 00:14:51.780 align:middle line:84%
And one of the side effects
was people would lose weight

00:14:51.780 --> 00:14:54.900 align:middle line:90%
in these Teslatron units.

00:14:54.900 --> 00:14:58.320 align:middle line:84%
And the scientists still did
not know, even though it worked,

00:14:58.320 --> 00:15:00.600 align:middle line:90%
where that substance was going.

00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:02.370 align:middle line:84%
So I was always
thinking, someone

00:15:02.370 --> 00:15:04.530 align:middle line:84%
over in Arturis or
something all of a sudden

00:15:04.530 --> 00:15:08.143 align:middle line:84%
just got a pound of fat slapped
in their face or something.

00:15:08.143 --> 00:15:09.560 align:middle line:84%
And they're like,
all right, we're

00:15:09.560 --> 00:15:12.098 align:middle line:84%
going to shut those guys
down over there on Earth.

00:15:12.098 --> 00:15:13.890 align:middle line:84%
Just because you're
throwing a bowling ball

00:15:13.890 --> 00:15:16.230 align:middle line:84%
through a field
of energy and you

00:15:16.230 --> 00:15:20.040 align:middle line:84%
don't know where it's going,
that's a little disrespectful.

00:15:20.040 --> 00:15:22.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, you get a call later
saying, hey, cut that out.

00:15:22.530 --> 00:15:24.540 align:middle line:90%
>> Hey, you gotta stop that.

00:15:24.540 --> 00:15:27.540 align:middle line:84%
Do we have temporal weapons
today that you know about?

00:15:27.540 --> 00:15:30.450 align:middle line:84%
>> As far as I understand,
we're experimenting with them.

00:15:30.450 --> 00:15:31.990 align:middle line:84%
I've never used
one in the field,

00:15:31.990 --> 00:15:34.560 align:middle line:84%
but we're definitely
experimenting with them.

00:15:34.560 --> 00:15:36.810 align:middle line:84%
>> And what about these
frequency modulators that you

00:15:36.810 --> 00:15:39.000 align:middle line:90%
talked about?

00:15:39.000 --> 00:15:42.750 align:middle line:84%
>> The frequency modulators--
so they modulate frequencies,

00:15:42.750 --> 00:15:46.530 align:middle line:84%
which makes them a fairly
universal tool depending

00:15:46.530 --> 00:15:51.810 align:middle line:84%
on what you need to disrupt
and/or try and protect.

00:15:51.810 --> 00:15:53.370 align:middle line:84%
If you're trying to
protect something

00:15:53.370 --> 00:15:56.460 align:middle line:84%
with a field modulation,
it can work for that.

00:15:56.460 --> 00:15:59.040 align:middle line:84%
If you're trying to disrupt
another energy frequency,

00:15:59.040 --> 00:16:02.640 align:middle line:84%
whether it's psionic or
electronic, electromagnetic,

00:16:02.640 --> 00:16:06.330 align:middle line:84%
technological, there
are ways in which

00:16:06.330 --> 00:16:09.770 align:middle line:84%
you can use a frequency
modulator that

00:16:09.770 --> 00:16:13.467 align:middle line:84%
can make internal
combustion engines not work.

00:16:13.467 --> 00:16:15.050 align:middle line:84%
You can send out a
frequency that will

00:16:15.050 --> 00:16:17.000 align:middle line:90%
make electric motors not work.

00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:20.510 align:middle line:84%
You can use frequency
modulation to heat up

00:16:20.510 --> 00:16:25.040 align:middle line:84%
mechanical parts in a gun
so that a gun won't work.

00:16:25.040 --> 00:16:27.830 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot of different
uses for frequency modulation--

00:16:27.830 --> 00:16:30.290 align:middle line:84%
more than I could list,
to be honest with you.

00:16:30.290 --> 00:16:33.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, were the weapons that
the humans used in the SSP,

00:16:33.110 --> 00:16:35.780 align:middle line:84%
were they comparable
to the ETs'?

00:16:35.780 --> 00:16:39.980 align:middle line:84%
>> I would say, at this point,
we make better stuff than most

00:16:39.980 --> 00:16:40.880 align:middle line:90%
of everybody else.

00:16:40.880 --> 00:16:46.940 align:middle line:84%
So while there are weapons out
there that far surpass our own,

00:16:46.940 --> 00:16:49.550 align:middle line:84%
there are many tools
and weapons out there

00:16:49.550 --> 00:16:51.960 align:middle line:84%
that don't compare to
the stuff that we make.

00:16:51.960 --> 00:16:55.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, were any of these
completely different than

00:16:55.850 --> 00:16:57.260 align:middle line:90%
anything you've seen here?

00:16:57.260 --> 00:16:58.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:16:58.060 --> 00:17:02.100 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there was actually a
species that had a little--

00:17:02.100 --> 00:17:03.560 align:middle line:90%
looked like a little magic wand.

00:17:03.560 --> 00:17:06.200 align:middle line:84%
You can barely see it-- a little
metal rod about like that.

00:17:06.200 --> 00:17:08.119 align:middle line:84%
And it had, apparently,
three settings.

00:17:08.119 --> 00:17:09.619 align:middle line:90%
And it could either--

00:17:09.619 --> 00:17:11.720 align:middle line:84%
it was basically a
frequency modulator.

00:17:11.720 --> 00:17:15.859 align:middle line:84%
And it either modulate with
the magnesium in your body

00:17:15.859 --> 00:17:20.690 align:middle line:84%
or the potassium in
your body or the iodine.

00:17:20.690 --> 00:17:24.950 align:middle line:84%
So the magnesium, essentially,
because your magnesium

00:17:24.950 --> 00:17:27.920 align:middle line:84%
receptors in your central
nervous system are the relaxing

00:17:27.920 --> 00:17:31.070 align:middle line:84%
receptors-- that's a stunner
can knock someone out--

00:17:31.070 --> 00:17:36.248 align:middle line:84%
the sodium resonator can
cause incredible pain,

00:17:36.248 --> 00:17:38.540 align:middle line:84%
because it's activating all
your central nervous system

00:17:38.540 --> 00:17:39.440 align:middle line:90%
receptors.

00:17:39.440 --> 00:17:42.380 align:middle line:84%
And apparently, the
iodine frequency

00:17:42.380 --> 00:17:44.870 align:middle line:84%
causes your hemoglobin
to start to pop,

00:17:44.870 --> 00:17:48.570 align:middle line:84%
and you basically
rupture blood vessels--

00:17:48.570 --> 00:17:50.240 align:middle line:90%
>> You hemolize inside of you.

00:17:50.240 --> 00:17:52.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, you basically
blow apart on the inside.

00:17:52.320 --> 00:17:53.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Can anyone--

00:17:53.120 --> 00:17:55.370 align:middle line:84%
>> As far as I know, we don't
have anything like that.

00:17:55.370 --> 00:17:57.890 align:middle line:84%
>> Right, but can a human
use that or only the ET?

00:17:57.890 --> 00:18:01.970 align:middle line:84%
>> The weapon itself
is tuned to their DNA.

00:18:01.970 --> 00:18:05.900 align:middle line:84%
So I mean, if you pick it up and
it doesn't have the right DNA

00:18:05.900 --> 00:18:08.610 align:middle line:84%
to match with the
weapon, you can't use it.

00:18:08.610 --> 00:18:11.700 align:middle line:84%
So I couldn't pick up one
of those weapons and use it.

00:18:11.700 --> 00:18:14.190 align:middle line:84%
But again, if we
developed one, we could.

00:18:14.190 --> 00:18:16.460 align:middle line:84%
But I don't know that we're
using those or developing

00:18:16.460 --> 00:18:17.670 align:middle line:90%
those at this time.

00:18:17.670 --> 00:18:22.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Are any of the weapons
that you have utilized reverse

00:18:22.250 --> 00:18:25.490 align:middle line:84%
engineered from
extraterrestrials?

00:18:25.490 --> 00:18:28.190 align:middle line:84%
>> Pretty much all of them,
as far as I understand.

00:18:28.190 --> 00:18:30.920 align:middle line:84%
The fundamental basis
of all of our technology

00:18:30.920 --> 00:18:33.620 align:middle line:84%
comes from somebody else's
technology originally.

00:18:33.620 --> 00:18:37.220 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course, we add our
own creative potential to that

00:18:37.220 --> 00:18:41.720 align:middle line:84%
and modify them in ways that
we think are specific to us,

00:18:41.720 --> 00:18:46.610 align:middle line:84%
but pretty much every technology
that we have at this point

00:18:46.610 --> 00:18:49.900 align:middle line:84%
probably was given to us
by someone else before,

00:18:49.900 --> 00:18:53.270 align:middle line:84%
or at least some component of it
was given to us by someone else

00:18:53.270 --> 00:18:55.460 align:middle line:84%
before we could
develop it ourselves.

00:18:55.460 --> 00:18:57.890 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, I agree that most
technology that we have

00:18:57.890 --> 00:18:58.820 align:middle line:90%
on the planet--

00:18:58.820 --> 00:19:00.050 align:middle line:90%
we're just not that smart.

00:19:00.050 --> 00:19:00.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Most.

00:19:00.850 --> 00:19:01.800 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, most.

00:19:01.800 --> 00:19:03.550 align:middle line:84%
>> Now we talked about
these cool weapons,

00:19:03.550 --> 00:19:09.230 align:middle line:84%
we talked about utilizing rifles
and plasma rifles and railguns,

00:19:09.230 --> 00:19:12.800 align:middle line:84%
but how about hand-to-hand
combat weapons?

00:19:12.800 --> 00:19:15.650 align:middle line:84%
Did you ever see any
special knives or swords?

00:19:15.650 --> 00:19:16.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh yeah.

00:19:16.450 --> 00:19:17.900 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we were
certainly trained

00:19:17.900 --> 00:19:21.500 align:middle line:84%
in all hand-to-hand
weapons, all melee weapons.

00:19:21.500 --> 00:19:24.140 align:middle line:84%
We used to use something
called the personal utility

00:19:24.140 --> 00:19:27.320 align:middle line:84%
tool or the putter,
which is basically

00:19:27.320 --> 00:19:31.560 align:middle line:84%
a very heavy handle
with a blade on it

00:19:31.560 --> 00:19:35.450 align:middle line:84%
that's like a reverse guillotine
blade made out of some alloy.

00:19:35.450 --> 00:19:39.110 align:middle line:84%
So you can hit somebody in
the head with it like an ax

00:19:39.110 --> 00:19:41.420 align:middle line:84%
or slice off body
parts, and it's

00:19:41.420 --> 00:19:44.630 align:middle line:84%
got a spike on the
palm and a spike

00:19:44.630 --> 00:19:46.340 align:middle line:84%
on the back of the
top of the head of it.

00:19:46.340 --> 00:19:48.710 align:middle line:90%
It's very, very vicious.

00:19:48.710 --> 00:19:49.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Sounds very brutal.

00:19:49.710 --> 00:19:51.170 align:middle line:90%
>> It's very brutal.

00:19:51.170 --> 00:19:56.330 align:middle line:84%
In the hand of an exosuit
with that extra hydraulics

00:19:56.330 --> 00:20:00.740 align:middle line:84%
in your muscles, you can take
limbs off, and it's brutal.

00:20:00.740 --> 00:20:02.510 align:middle line:90%
Makes a lot of crunching noises.

00:20:02.510 --> 00:20:06.200 align:middle line:84%
>> What about chemically
propelled weapons?

00:20:06.200 --> 00:20:08.900 align:middle line:84%
>> There are species
that still use them.

00:20:08.900 --> 00:20:10.790 align:middle line:84%
We don't typically
use them anymore

00:20:10.790 --> 00:20:13.180 align:middle line:84%
because they're just
less effective than all

00:20:13.180 --> 00:20:14.180 align:middle line:90%
the other tools we have.

00:20:14.180 --> 00:20:16.280 align:middle line:84%
But we've encountered species
who are still using chemically

00:20:16.280 --> 00:20:17.420 align:middle line:90%
propelled weapons.

00:20:17.420 --> 00:20:20.030 align:middle line:84%
>> Let's talk about the weapons
that you have encountered that

00:20:20.030 --> 00:20:21.320 align:middle line:90%
are not human.

00:20:21.320 --> 00:20:24.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Probably one of the more
interesting and common weapons

00:20:24.710 --> 00:20:29.450 align:middle line:84%
is what we consider a low-grade
plasma gun or plasma weapon,

00:20:29.450 --> 00:20:31.370 align:middle line:90%
which is like a lightning gun.

00:20:31.370 --> 00:20:33.355 align:middle line:84%
So it shoots a
beam, a plasma beam,

00:20:33.355 --> 00:20:35.105 align:middle line:84%
which is like a lightning
bolt, basically,

00:20:35.105 --> 00:20:36.440 align:middle line:90%
out of the end of it.

00:20:36.440 --> 00:20:37.920 align:middle line:90%
That's actually fairly common.

00:20:37.920 --> 00:20:39.628 align:middle line:84%
There are a lot of
species that use them.

00:20:39.628 --> 00:20:42.980 align:middle line:84%
Turns out they're really
easy to make and have

00:20:42.980 --> 00:20:44.810 align:middle line:90%
a very low failure rate.

00:20:44.810 --> 00:20:48.410 align:middle line:84%
>> How do you think ETs know
how our bodies would respond

00:20:48.410 --> 00:20:49.770 align:middle line:90%
to the weapons that they make?

00:20:49.770 --> 00:20:50.570 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:20:50.570 --> 00:20:55.083 align:middle line:84%
Well, let's talk about
gases, viruses, bacterias.

00:20:55.083 --> 00:20:57.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Sure, and probably
the same way that we do,

00:20:57.000 --> 00:21:02.300 align:middle line:84%
by testing them on biological
entities that we want to test

00:21:02.300 --> 00:21:03.440 align:middle line:90%
that stuff onto.

00:21:03.440 --> 00:21:07.920 align:middle line:84%
So if we want to engineer
a virus, or bacteria,

00:21:07.920 --> 00:21:11.730 align:middle line:84%
or gaseous substance that's
specific towards a certain

00:21:11.730 --> 00:21:14.190 align:middle line:84%
extraterrestrial
biological form,

00:21:14.190 --> 00:21:16.410 align:middle line:84%
or if we have some
general knowledge

00:21:16.410 --> 00:21:19.740 align:middle line:84%
about general biological
forms and we come up

00:21:19.740 --> 00:21:23.070 align:middle line:84%
with a biological species that
matches one of the templates,

00:21:23.070 --> 00:21:25.200 align:middle line:84%
then we can start
from there instead

00:21:25.200 --> 00:21:27.210 align:middle line:90%
of starting from square one.

00:21:27.210 --> 00:21:29.400 align:middle line:84%
But we absolutely
have the ability

00:21:29.400 --> 00:21:37.440 align:middle line:84%
to design these tools for
mass, mass, mass combat.

00:21:37.440 --> 00:21:42.930 align:middle line:84%
So when we feel like we have
to use mass-extinction weapons,

00:21:42.930 --> 00:21:46.650 align:middle line:84%
use weapons of mass
destruction, then we will.

00:21:46.650 --> 00:21:49.740 align:middle line:84%
It is a preference
more than anything

00:21:49.740 --> 00:21:52.920 align:middle line:84%
else because the
use of these tools

00:21:52.920 --> 00:21:57.580 align:middle line:84%
often causes more harm and
more death than you want.

00:21:57.580 --> 00:22:00.240 align:middle line:84%
And there are
intergalactic bodies

00:22:00.240 --> 00:22:03.030 align:middle line:90%
who can investigate war crimes.

00:22:03.030 --> 00:22:09.340 align:middle line:84%
And so we know that if we
handicap ourselves a little bit

00:22:09.340 --> 00:22:13.300 align:middle line:84%
and don't do the maximum damage
that we could possibly do--

00:22:13.300 --> 00:22:14.750 align:middle line:84%
because we're very
good at that--

00:22:14.750 --> 00:22:16.930 align:middle line:84%
that we're going to
be less likely to come

00:22:16.930 --> 00:22:18.970 align:middle line:84%
into legal entanglements
later and have

00:22:18.970 --> 00:22:21.400 align:middle line:84%
to answer to some sort
of intergalactic tribunal

00:22:21.400 --> 00:22:23.800 align:middle line:84%
on war crimes or something
like that as long

00:22:23.800 --> 00:22:29.140 align:middle line:84%
as we behave ourselves according
to certain acceptable rules

00:22:29.140 --> 00:22:30.510 align:middle line:90%
of engagement.

00:22:30.510 --> 00:22:34.510 align:middle line:84%
>> Why are these weapons not
fine-tuned so we don't take out

00:22:34.510 --> 00:22:38.560 align:middle line:84%
extra buildings,
extra innocent beings?

00:22:38.560 --> 00:22:41.670 align:middle line:84%
It sounds like we should
have that type of technology.

00:22:41.670 --> 00:22:43.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, sometimes we do.

00:22:43.600 --> 00:22:46.660 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes that's an option, but
sometimes it's not an option.

00:22:46.660 --> 00:22:50.410 align:middle line:84%
Like I said, shielding around
facilities and buildings

00:22:50.410 --> 00:22:53.950 align:middle line:84%
makes it difficult to
use weaponry from ships.

00:22:53.950 --> 00:22:57.370 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we have destroyers
that can fire giant particle

00:22:57.370 --> 00:23:00.790 align:middle line:84%
beams from space,
and giant missiles

00:23:00.790 --> 00:23:03.380 align:middle line:84%
and torpedoes from space,
and quantum bombs and things.

00:23:03.380 --> 00:23:05.050 align:middle line:90%
We do have those abilities.

00:23:05.050 --> 00:23:07.320 align:middle line:84%
It's just that they're
not always an option,

00:23:07.320 --> 00:23:08.920 align:middle line:84%
nor again are they
always preferred.

00:23:08.920 --> 00:23:13.750 align:middle line:84%
So it's one of those things
where, probably like we should,

00:23:13.750 --> 00:23:16.550 align:middle line:84%
we only use them when
they're really necessary.

00:23:16.550 --> 00:23:20.380 align:middle line:84%
We would rather send in
a small group of people

00:23:20.380 --> 00:23:26.050 align:middle line:84%
to do something very efficiently
than do something that's kills

00:23:26.050 --> 00:23:27.290 align:middle line:90%
off a lot of people.

00:23:27.290 --> 00:23:28.800 align:middle line:84%
>> It's based off
of the mission.

00:23:28.800 --> 00:23:29.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Pretty much.

00:23:29.600 --> 00:23:30.820 align:middle line:90%
>> Each mission is different.

00:23:30.820 --> 00:23:34.750 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, and we understand
that, as a warrior species--

00:23:34.750 --> 00:23:35.800 align:middle line:90%
because we are.

00:23:35.800 --> 00:23:37.600 align:middle line:84%
Our military leaders
have accepted

00:23:37.600 --> 00:23:39.460 align:middle line:84%
that among the
intergalactic community

00:23:39.460 --> 00:23:41.080 align:middle line:90%
we're a warrior species.

00:23:41.080 --> 00:23:43.828 align:middle line:84%
We like conflict,
and we like fighting

00:23:43.828 --> 00:23:46.120 align:middle line:84%
more than some other species
do, and we're better at it

00:23:46.120 --> 00:23:47.538 align:middle line:90%
than some other species.

00:23:47.538 --> 00:23:49.330 align:middle line:84%
So it's understood and
accepted that that's

00:23:49.330 --> 00:23:51.205 align:middle line:84%
what we're going to
spend quite a bit of time

00:23:51.205 --> 00:23:52.990 align:middle line:84%
doing because that's
what we're good at.

00:23:52.990 --> 00:23:56.170 align:middle line:84%
But we also see through
the intergalactic community

00:23:56.170 --> 00:23:59.350 align:middle line:84%
that warrior species can end
up with different reputations

00:23:59.350 --> 00:24:01.630 align:middle line:84%
depending on how they
go about their business.

00:24:01.630 --> 00:24:03.920 align:middle line:84%
And from looking
at other species,

00:24:03.920 --> 00:24:06.660 align:middle line:84%
we don't want to have
a bad reputation.

00:24:06.660 --> 00:24:12.480 align:middle line:84%
So we believe that
measured responses

00:24:12.480 --> 00:24:15.000 align:middle line:84%
make it more clear that
we're not barbarians

00:24:15.000 --> 00:24:16.680 align:middle line:84%
when we engage in
military conflict,

00:24:16.680 --> 00:24:19.200 align:middle line:84%
that we're not just hitting
people on the head with clubs

00:24:19.200 --> 00:24:20.910 align:middle line:84%
and killing as many
people as possible

00:24:20.910 --> 00:24:25.170 align:middle line:84%
like thugs and barbarians,
that we're being strategic,

00:24:25.170 --> 00:24:28.230 align:middle line:84%
surgical, precise
whenever possible.

00:24:28.230 --> 00:24:30.030 align:middle line:84%
>> Do they know
we're from Earth?

00:24:30.030 --> 00:24:32.570 align:middle line:90%
Do they know you're from Earth?

00:24:32.570 --> 00:24:33.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Sometimes.

00:24:33.520 --> 00:24:34.320 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes no.

00:24:34.320 --> 00:24:36.390 align:middle line:90%
It really depends.

00:24:36.390 --> 00:24:41.300 align:middle line:84%
I mean, if you're another
species on another planet,

00:24:41.300 --> 00:24:46.165 align:middle line:84%
and soldiers in exosuits that
are using active camouflage

00:24:46.165 --> 00:24:47.540 align:middle line:84%
so they're
essentially invisible,

00:24:47.540 --> 00:24:49.610 align:middle line:84%
and you can't see them,
and you don't know what

00:24:49.610 --> 00:24:52.130 align:middle line:84%
the technology is, and you're
not sure where they're from,

00:24:52.130 --> 00:24:54.710 align:middle line:84%
that's as mysterious
as anything could be.

00:24:54.710 --> 00:24:57.860 align:middle line:84%
It might take some time to
figure out, who was that?

00:24:57.860 --> 00:24:59.790 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:24:59.790 --> 00:25:01.970 align:middle line:84%
But if they don't have
any previous experience

00:25:01.970 --> 00:25:04.040 align:middle line:84%
or they haven't
heard the rumors,

00:25:04.040 --> 00:25:06.200 align:middle line:84%
then they might not
know who it is at first.

00:25:06.200 --> 00:25:09.000 align:middle line:84%
>> How does that
camouflage work?

00:25:09.000 --> 00:25:12.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, there's a few
different methodologies.

00:25:12.830 --> 00:25:16.160 align:middle line:84%
The older technology
