image of what's behind you.

00:25:20.360 --> 00:25:22.490 align:middle line:84%
So it uses a lot of
little mini-cameras

00:25:22.490 --> 00:25:25.520 align:middle line:84%
on 360 degrees on
the suit with a lot

00:25:25.520 --> 00:25:27.440 align:middle line:90%
of little mini-projectors.

00:25:27.440 --> 00:25:30.140 align:middle line:84%
So these little projecting
cameras and screens

00:25:30.140 --> 00:25:31.100 align:middle line:90%
are very, very tiny.

00:25:31.100 --> 00:25:33.920 align:middle line:84%
And they're all linked
together so that, essentially,

00:25:33.920 --> 00:25:36.380 align:middle line:84%
when someone's looking
at you, they're

00:25:36.380 --> 00:25:40.850 align:middle line:84%
seeing what's behind you,
now, not in a perfect way--

00:25:40.850 --> 00:25:41.660 align:middle line:90%
pretty good.

00:25:41.660 --> 00:25:43.860 align:middle line:90%
We sort of think of it as--

00:25:43.860 --> 00:25:44.660 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:25:44.660 --> 00:25:47.350 align:middle line:84%
There's probably a franchise
that I can't use by name.

00:25:47.350 --> 00:25:48.150 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:25:48.150 --> 00:25:51.530 align:middle line:84%
>> But we've all seen the sort
of invisible that you can kind

00:25:51.530 --> 00:25:52.880 align:middle line:90%
of see.

00:25:52.880 --> 00:25:54.770 align:middle line:84%
So that would be the
older active camouflage.

00:25:54.770 --> 00:25:59.120 align:middle line:84%
We have some newer stuff
that if I was wearing that,

00:25:59.120 --> 00:26:02.665 align:middle line:84%
I could potentially walk through
the room with people around,

00:26:02.665 --> 00:26:04.790 align:middle line:84%
