But there is
nothing in this suit

00:29:43.310 --> 00:29:46.460 align:middle line:84%
that would repair
cutting something off

00:29:46.460 --> 00:29:48.830 align:middle line:90%
with a heated plasma torch.

00:29:48.830 --> 00:29:50.180 align:middle line:90%
It's just going to--

00:29:50.180 --> 00:29:51.110 align:middle line:90%
bye, tissue.

00:29:51.110 --> 00:29:52.070 align:middle line:90%
Bye-bye.

00:29:52.070 --> 00:29:55.070 align:middle line:84%
And you've got to regenerate
it, make some new stuff.

00:29:55.070 --> 00:29:58.570 align:middle line:84%
>> If we used a plasma
weapon on each other,

00:29:58.570 --> 00:30:00.660 align:middle line:84%
do we have something to
regenerate that wound?

00:30:00.660 --> 00:30:01.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:30:01.460 --> 00:30:02.362 align:middle line:90%
We can fix anything.

00:30:02.362 --> 00:30:04.070 align:middle line:84%
We have the technology
that can literally

00:30:04.070 --> 00:30:08.120 align:middle line:84%
fix anything, any
amount of damage,

00:30:08.120 --> 00:30:11.420 align:middle line:84%
any amount of percentage of
body-tissue damage anywhere.

00:30:11.420 --> 00:30:12.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Is that the
holographic beds--

00:30:12.980 --> 00:30:13.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:30:13.280 --> 00:30:13.910 align:middle line:90%
>> --you speak of?

00:30:13.910 --> 00:30:14.780 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep.

00:30:14.780 --> 00:30:17.180 align:middle line:84%
That's at least the
quickest, most efficient

00:30:17.180 --> 00:30:19.120 align:middle line:90%
that I've ever used.

00:30:19.120 --> 00:30:22.070 align:middle line:84%
>> When is humanity
going to see these beds?

00:30:22.070 --> 00:30:24.605 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, that's a good question.

00:30:24.605 --> 00:30:29.960 align:middle line:84%
I do have a chief
engineer and a CFO.

00:30:29.960 --> 00:30:32.630 align:middle line:84%
And we have put
together a small startup

00:30:32.630 --> 00:30:36.452 align:middle line:84%
to get the funding
to begin the process,

00:30:36.452 --> 00:30:37.910 align:middle line:84%
to do the research
and development,

00:30:37.910 --> 00:30:41.210 align:middle line:84%
to build the components,
to replicate terrestrial

00:30:41.210 --> 00:30:43.160 align:middle line:84%
technology in the
civilian world.

00:30:43.160 --> 00:30:48.140 align:middle line:84%
We think from starting
point to prototype

00:30:48.140 --> 00:30:49.833 align:middle line:90%
is three to five years.

00:30:49.833 --> 00:30:52.250 align:middle line:84%
There is some conversation
I've heard other people talking

00:30:52.250 --> 00:30:55.250 align:middle line:84%
about, some of
these technologies

00:30:55.250 --> 00:30:59.220 align:middle line:84%
or similar technologies that
are going to come out next year.

00:30:59.220 --> 00:31:00.620 align:middle line:90%
I don't think that's happening.

00:31:00.620 --> 00:31:06.230 align:middle line:84%
But we would think
that with the funding

00:31:06.230 --> 00:31:08.570 align:middle line:84%
that we're going
to get-- and this

00:31:08.570 --> 00:31:10.670 align:middle line:84%
is something we've been
working on for years,

00:31:10.670 --> 00:31:13.730 align:middle line:84%
and my CFO has been giving
me a lot of confidence

00:31:13.730 --> 00:31:16.880 align:middle line:84%
that we should have our
startup funding sometime

00:31:16.880 --> 00:31:19.310 align:middle line:84%
this year so we can
begin the process soon.

00:31:19.310 --> 00:31:22.070 align:middle line:84%
So I'd like to think a prototype
in three to five years.

00:31:22.070 --> 00:31:25.020 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to think a
commercial product within 10.

00:31:25.020 --> 00:31:26.450 align:middle line:84%
Those are conservative
estimates.

00:31:26.450 --> 00:31:29.978 align:middle line:84%
As Buckminster Fuller said, if
you want to change something--

00:31:29.978 --> 00:31:31.520 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to paraphrase
here-- if you

00:31:31.520 --> 00:31:34.145 align:middle line:84%
want to change the world, if you
want to make something better,

00:31:34.145 --> 00:31:36.740 align:middle line:84%
you don't just say,
let's do it this way.

00:31:36.740 --> 00:31:38.270 align:middle line:90%
You create a better option.

00:31:38.270 --> 00:31:39.410 align:middle line:90%
You create a better method.

00:31:39.410 --> 00:31:42.170 align:middle line:84%
You create a better
tool and then wait

00:31:42.170 --> 00:31:44.900 align:middle line:84%
for the rest of the world
to adapt and pick up.

00:31:44.900 --> 00:31:48.260 align:middle line:84%
Because if you make something
that's more cost-effective

00:31:48.260 --> 00:31:52.370 align:middle line:84%
and works better than any
other technology that you have,

00:31:52.370 --> 00:31:55.310 align:middle line:84%
well, the marketplace is
going to eventually want that.

00:31:55.310 --> 00:31:58.640 align:middle line:84%
So if you lost your arm,
it would be cheaper for me

00:31:58.640 --> 00:32:01.410 align:middle line:84%
to put you in a holobed
and regrow your arm

00:32:01.410 --> 00:32:03.290 align:middle line:84%
than it would be actually
to design a custom

00:32:03.290 --> 00:32:04.240 align:middle line:90%
prosthetic for you.

00:32:04.240 --> 00:32:05.700 align:middle line:90%
It would actually be cheaper.

00:32:05.700 --> 00:32:08.930 align:middle line:84%
So once you demonstrate that
you have something better,

00:32:08.930 --> 00:32:12.980 align:middle line:84%
that it's more cost-effective,
that it's more efficient,

00:32:12.980 --> 00:32:14.730 align:middle line:84%
people will just
eventually switch.

00:32:14.730 --> 00:32:16.430 align:middle line:84%
So we think that
there-- we don't--

00:32:16.430 --> 00:32:19.080 align:middle line:84%
not saying there's not going to
be some uphill struggle there.

00:32:19.080 --> 00:32:21.260 align:middle line:84%
But we think, in
the end, the tool

00:32:21.260 --> 00:32:24.065 align:middle line:84%
itself wins because it's
better than the other tools

00:32:24.065 --> 00:32:24.865 align:middle line:90%
that we have.

00:32:24.865 --> 00:32:26.810 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, I 100% agree.

00:32:26.810 --> 00:32:30.200 align:middle line:84%
And I've, of course, experienced
that with a lot of my devices

00:32:30.200 --> 00:32:32.580 align:middle line:84%
that I have invented that I
was shunned for for years.

00:32:32.580 --> 00:32:33.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:32:33.380 --> 00:32:37.280 align:middle line:84%
>> But once they saw that
it worked and you make it

00:32:37.280 --> 00:32:39.380 align:middle line:90%
cost-effective--

00:32:39.380 --> 00:32:41.480 align:middle line:84%
so I think you're on a
great trajectory for that.

00:32:41.480 --> 00:32:42.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:32:42.280 --> 00:32:45.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you see humankind and
our allies moving more towards

00:32:45.330 --> 00:32:46.130 align:middle line:90%
peace?

00:32:46.130 --> 00:32:49.580 align:middle line:84%
Or is it just getting ready
for some sort of perpetual war?

00:32:49.580 --> 00:32:54.440 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I can tell you what
the goal of the military at this

00:32:54.440 --> 00:32:55.520 align:middle line:90%
time is.

00:32:55.520 --> 00:32:59.810 align:middle line:84%
The military understands
that without conflict, they

00:32:59.810 --> 00:33:02.480 align:middle line:84%
have no purpose,
which has been part

00:33:02.480 --> 00:33:05.330 align:middle line:84%
of the problem for
the last 100 years

00:33:05.330 --> 00:33:08.150 align:middle line:84%
that we have to keep things
going, keep conflicts going.

00:33:08.150 --> 00:33:10.250 align:middle line:84%
Because if we
don't, then they'll

00:33:10.250 --> 00:33:13.280 align:middle line:84%
just cease to exist and go away,
and that's not what we want.

00:33:13.280 --> 00:33:14.660 align:middle line:90%
>> And there's money to be made.

00:33:14.660 --> 00:33:15.993 align:middle line:90%
>> And there's money to be made.

00:33:15.993 --> 00:33:18.380 align:middle line:84%
But we also are seeing
the long-term benefits

00:33:18.380 --> 00:33:22.175 align:middle line:84%
of having a strong defense and
that to have a strong defense,

00:33:22.175 --> 00:33:24.050 align:middle line:84%
you have to keep going,
and going, and going.

00:33:24.050 --> 00:33:25.550 align:middle line:84%
Now, what we'd like
to see though is

00:33:25.550 --> 00:33:27.980 align:middle line:84%
we would like to see
military conflict

00:33:27.980 --> 00:33:30.650 align:middle line:90%
on planet Earth come to zero.

00:33:30.650 --> 00:33:31.520 align:middle line:90%
We'd like that.

00:33:31.520 --> 00:33:34.340 align:middle line:84%
We would like to see that
human beings on planet Earth

00:33:34.340 --> 00:33:37.760 align:middle line:84%
no longer fight, kill, use
weapons of destruction and mass

00:33:37.760 --> 00:33:40.160 align:middle line:84%
destruction against each
other to solve conflicts.

00:33:40.160 --> 00:33:42.740 align:middle line:84%
We would like to take all
of our military technology

00:33:42.740 --> 00:33:44.720 align:middle line:90%
and focus it outside.

00:33:44.720 --> 00:33:47.690 align:middle line:84%
We think if we're focusing
it outside of our own planet,

00:33:47.690 --> 00:33:49.640 align:middle line:84%
then we don't have to
live that way here.

00:33:49.640 --> 00:33:54.260 align:middle line:84%
We can take that
perpetual necessity away

00:33:54.260 --> 00:33:57.320 align:middle line:84%
from the planetary function,
and we can move it outward.

00:33:57.320 --> 00:34:00.320 align:middle line:90%
Because let's just be honest.

00:34:00.320 --> 00:34:02.690 align:middle line:84%
Now that we're in the
intergalactic community,

00:34:02.690 --> 00:34:06.230 align:middle line:84%
the potential of military
threats are near limitless.

00:34:06.230 --> 00:34:08.090 align:middle line:84%
The potential of
military threats

00:34:08.090 --> 00:34:10.610 align:middle line:84%
that are stronger and
more capable than what

00:34:10.610 --> 00:34:13.114 align:middle line:84%
we can do currently today
are near limitless as we

00:34:13.114 --> 00:34:14.239 align:middle line:90%
go farther and farther out.

00:34:14.239 --> 00:34:20.330 align:middle line:84%
So the need to continue
to develop a strong space

00:34:20.330 --> 00:34:23.840 align:middle line:84%
military force is going to be
necessary for the next 10,000

00:34:23.840 --> 00:34:24.780 align:middle line:90%
years.

00:34:24.780 --> 00:34:26.750 align:middle line:90%
So that's just the way it is.

00:34:26.750 --> 00:34:29.000 align:middle line:84%
I mean, some people want to
call that "perpetual war."

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:30.020 align:middle line:90%
I don't.

00:34:30.020 --> 00:34:32.090 align:middle line:84%
I call that
"perpetual necessity."

00:34:32.090 --> 00:34:34.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you feel more pessimistic
or optimistic about where

00:34:34.730 --> 00:34:36.160 align:middle line:90%
humanity is going?

00:34:36.160 --> 00:34:36.960 align:middle line:90%
>> Both.

00:34:36.960 --> 00:34:39.139 align:middle line:84%
I think that we are
currently moving

00:34:39.139 --> 00:34:41.960 align:middle line:84%
toward some things that
are going to get worse

00:34:41.960 --> 00:34:43.409 align:middle line:90%
before they get better.

00:34:43.409 --> 00:34:47.960 align:middle line:84%
But the arc towards improvement
I think is well planned out.

00:34:47.960 --> 00:34:51.170 align:middle line:84%
So these aren't surprises
that are coming up.

00:34:51.170 --> 00:34:52.489 align:middle line:90%
We're like, oh, what do we do?

00:34:52.489 --> 00:34:58.550 align:middle line:84%
These are knowns that we know
are sort of inevitably coming.

00:34:58.550 --> 00:34:59.878 align:middle line:90%
The bill is coming due.

00:34:59.878 --> 00:35:00.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Just a matter of time.

00:35:00.920 --> 00:35:02.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, the bill is
coming due on some things.

00:35:02.660 --> 00:35:04.550 align:middle line:84%
And we know there's going to
be some changes with that,

00:35:04.550 --> 00:35:06.092 align:middle line:84%
and we think that
there's going to be

00:35:06.092 --> 00:35:11.280 align:middle line:84%
some moments in both domestic
and international conflict

00:35:11.280 --> 00:35:14.040 align:middle line:84%
which is going to increase
before it gets better.

00:35:14.040 --> 00:35:19.230 align:middle line:84%
But we are also looking at a
trajectory where in the next--

00:35:19.230 --> 00:35:20.520 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to go on a limb.

00:35:20.520 --> 00:35:22.500 align:middle line:84%
And I'll say, in
the next decade,

00:35:22.500 --> 00:35:26.100 align:middle line:84%
the goal is to get
past all of that

00:35:26.100 --> 00:35:28.800 align:middle line:84%
and stop fighting
amongst ourselves.

00:35:28.800 --> 00:35:33.490 align:middle line:84%
So fingers crossed that it
actually works out that way.

00:35:33.490 --> 00:35:36.910 align:middle line:84%
But I think we're-- it's going
to get a little uglier first.

00:35:36.910 --> 00:35:39.490 align:middle line:84%
But I think we have a
plan and a trajectory

00:35:39.490 --> 00:35:45.150 align:middle line:84%
to make it all work out so that
there's rainbows, and sunshine,

00:35:45.150 --> 00:35:46.560 align:middle line:90%
and puppies for everybody.

00:35:46.560 --> 00:35:49.590 align:middle line:84%
>> Randy, do you believe of any
benevolent ETs out there that

00:35:49.590 --> 00:35:52.390 align:middle line:84%
can actually affect
us spiritually?

00:35:52.390 --> 00:35:53.190 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah.

00:35:53.190 --> 00:35:55.200 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely, sure.

00:35:55.200 --> 00:35:59.250 align:middle line:84%
If I'm just to go by the reports
that we are hearing, I mean,

00:35:59.250 --> 00:36:01.710 align:middle line:84%
hundreds, hundreds
of species who

00:36:01.710 --> 00:36:06.300 align:middle line:84%
seem to be directly involved
in human terrestrial, spiritual

00:36:06.300 --> 00:36:09.667 align:middle line:84%
evolution and the spiritual
evolution of other species,

00:36:09.667 --> 00:36:11.250 align:middle line:84%
like that's what
they do all day long.

00:36:11.250 --> 00:36:12.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Where are they?

00:36:12.120 --> 00:36:15.810 align:middle line:84%
>> Most of them are either
operating out of phase

00:36:15.810 --> 00:36:18.810 align:middle line:84%
or in multidimensional,
interdimensional places

00:36:18.810 --> 00:36:23.480 align:middle line:84%
because it's safer for
them to work that way.

00:36:23.480 --> 00:36:25.440 align:middle line:84%
And that way, what
they really want to do

00:36:25.440 --> 00:36:27.430 align:middle line:90%
is work person to person.

00:36:27.430 --> 00:36:29.820 align:middle line:84%
These are the species
who would rather

00:36:29.820 --> 00:36:32.580 align:middle line:84%
identify an individual or
a number of individuals

00:36:32.580 --> 00:36:36.030 align:middle line:84%
and work with them one
on one than try and, say,

00:36:36.030 --> 00:36:39.190 align:middle line:84%
mass communicate or
mass educate people.

00:36:39.190 --> 00:36:42.420 align:middle line:84%
So by not engaging
necessarily with us

00:36:42.420 --> 00:36:45.630 align:middle line:84%
in a physical,
biological manner,

00:36:45.630 --> 00:36:48.660 align:middle line:84%
they can accomplish that
task much more easily

00:36:48.660 --> 00:36:51.030 align:middle line:84%
without scaring people,
or freaking people out,

00:36:51.030 --> 00:36:54.910 align:middle line:84%
or endangering themselves or
others by being physically

00:36:54.910 --> 00:36:55.710 align:middle line:90%
present with us.

00:36:55.710 --> 00:36:57.918 align:middle line:84%
So that's where the majority
of them seem to operate.

00:36:57.918 --> 00:37:02.760 align:middle line:84%
>> So these are benevolent
ETs that don't need weapons.

00:37:02.760 --> 00:37:06.570 align:middle line:84%
>> They have evolved to a place
where their ability to defend

00:37:06.570 --> 00:37:09.270 align:middle line:84%
themselves is such
that they don't.

00:37:09.270 --> 00:37:10.890 align:middle line:84%
There are species
who have evolved

00:37:10.890 --> 00:37:16.080 align:middle line:84%
to a place where if a fleet
of 10,000 destroyer ships

00:37:16.080 --> 00:37:19.230 align:middle line:84%
came to their planet, they would
just shift their planet out

00:37:19.230 --> 00:37:21.480 align:middle line:84%
of phase so that
those ships wouldn't

00:37:21.480 --> 00:37:23.620 align:middle line:90%
be able to affect them.

00:37:23.620 --> 00:37:26.460 align:middle line:84%
There's some pretty
advanced defenses

00:37:26.460 --> 00:37:28.470 align:middle line:84%
that once you achieve
that level, yeah,

00:37:28.470 --> 00:37:32.400 align:middle line:84%
you don't need a military so
much anymore because you're not

00:37:32.400 --> 00:37:35.970 align:middle line:84%
fighting force on force,
numbers on numbers.

00:37:35.970 --> 00:37:38.070 align:middle line:84%
You just have the
ability to say, well,

00:37:38.070 --> 00:37:42.420 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to just make it so you
can't touch my planet, period.

00:37:42.420 --> 00:37:46.843 align:middle line:84%
>> And that's just phasing in
and out of different dimensions

00:37:46.843 --> 00:37:48.010 align:middle line:90%
and reality, a whole planet?

00:37:48.010 --> 00:37:49.350 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep, yep, whole planet.

00:37:49.350 --> 00:37:54.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Have you seen this phasing
in and out of a defense system

00:37:54.330 --> 00:37:56.490 align:middle line:90%
that protects an entire planet?

00:37:56.490 --> 00:37:59.280 align:middle line:84%
And is that something
we're going to have?

00:37:59.280 --> 00:38:01.532 align:middle line:84%
>> I haven't seen it,
a whole planet do it.

00:38:01.532 --> 00:38:03.240 align:middle line:84%
I've heard about it
and read the reports.

00:38:03.240 --> 00:38:04.930 align:middle line:90%
I've seen a space station do it.

00:38:04.930 --> 00:38:07.710 align:middle line:84%
I've seen an entire space
station blink out of phase

00:38:07.710 --> 00:38:09.120 align:middle line:90%
so that it can't be attacked.

00:38:09.120 --> 00:38:11.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Are you talking about a moon
space station or a small space

00:38:11.980 --> 00:38:12.780 align:middle line:90%
station?

00:38:12.780 --> 00:38:16.260 align:middle line:84%
>> Like a big, floating
space station in space.

00:38:16.260 --> 00:38:21.942 align:middle line:84%
That would be the equivalent of
as big or bigger than Manhattan

00:38:21.942 --> 00:38:23.400 align:middle line:84%
or something like
that, pretty big.

00:38:23.400 --> 00:38:26.170 align:middle line:84%
>> And for the audience,
how does that scientifically

00:38:26.170 --> 00:38:26.970 align:middle line:90%
happen?

00:38:26.970 --> 00:38:29.790 align:middle line:84%
>> The molecules in your
body have a quantum frequency

00:38:29.790 --> 00:38:33.780 align:middle line:84%
to them that tells you what
dimension or frequency that

00:38:33.780 --> 00:38:35.920 align:middle line:84%
you're in, what
timespace you live in.

00:38:35.920 --> 00:38:37.980 align:middle line:84%
So if you have a
field that can alter

00:38:37.980 --> 00:38:40.890 align:middle line:84%
the frequency of every
molecule in an object,

00:38:40.890 --> 00:38:44.490 align:middle line:84%
you can shift that object
to any other phase.

00:38:44.490 --> 00:38:49.480 align:middle line:84%
And this is a very finely
tuned sort of modulation.

00:38:49.480 --> 00:38:53.430 align:middle line:84%
So you can tune yourself
to a coded frequency

00:38:53.430 --> 00:38:56.070 align:middle line:84%
that someone else is like, well,
we know they're out of phase,

00:38:56.070 --> 00:38:58.920 align:middle line:84%
but we can't figure out what
their exact frequency is,

00:38:58.920 --> 00:39:02.160 align:middle line:84%
so we can't exactly interact
with them physically.

00:39:02.160 --> 00:39:05.490 align:middle line:84%
Then it makes it a process of
the enemy trying to figure out

00:39:05.490 --> 00:39:07.450 align:middle line:90%
what the actual frequency is.

00:39:07.450 --> 00:39:11.490 align:middle line:84%
And there are species who have
such advanced systems that they

00:39:11.490 --> 00:39:14.830 align:middle line:84%
can rotate that
frequency very quickly.

00:39:14.830 --> 00:39:17.670 align:middle line:84%
And if you have a species
with the technology that can

00:39:17.670 --> 00:39:20.150 align:middle line:90%
rotate that quantum signature--

00:39:20.150 --> 00:39:22.110 align:middle line:84%
oh, I don't know--
every half a second,

00:39:22.110 --> 00:39:24.120 align:middle line:84%
that makes it almost
